summary: Modern Sister Starks Headcanon: When they were younger the Stark sister would preform Shakespeare plays. Sansa usually took the...
body: Modern Sister Starks Headcanon: When they were younger the Stark sister would preform Shakespeare plays. Sansa usually took the female lead(s) while Arya took the male lead/sides, but there were a few times she insisted on being a certain character. Most notably she demanded to be Rosalind (As you like it) and Viola (Twelfth Night)

summary:
It's not shippy or anything. Just something interesting I noticed when I rewatched S7.
Bran, giving Arya a Valyrian steel...
body:
It’s not shippy or anything. Just something interesting I noticed when I rewatched S7.

Bran, giving Arya a Valyrian steel dagger: It’s wasted on a cripple.

Kinda reminds me of Jaime, another cripple who made earlier mentioned boy crippled, giving Brienne, a very capable female warrior, a Valyrian steel sword.
